  },
  {
    q: "Should a hotel use the same coffee throughout the property?",
    a: "Not necessarily. A flagship restaurant might feature a local single-origin that tells a regional story. The all-day café might run a consistent espresso blend optimized for milk drinks. In-room offerings might use a curated ground or capsule program from the same roaster. Using the same roaster across touchpoints creates brand coherence; using different offerings within that relationship gives each experience its own character."
  },
  {
    q: "Do hotel guests actually notice coffee quality?",
    a: "Yes — consistently. Coffee is among the most frequently mentioned F&B items in hotel guest reviews, in both positive and negative contexts. A property with a genuinely excellent coffee program will see it reflected in reviews. A property with bad coffee will also see it reflected in reviews, often disproportionately, because a bad first cup in the morning sets the tone for the entire day."
